  <section class="section"><div class="wrap narrow">
    <h2>Signature Kitchen Suite, LG's 2016 luxury launch</h2>
    <p>Signature Kitchen Suite (SKS) is LG Electronics' dedicated luxury built-in appliance line, launched in 2016 to give LG a distinct positioning in the luxury-tier built-in market. Prior to SKS, LG competed broadly in mainstream premium/mass-market appliances, which made it difficult to compete head-to-head with Wolf + Thermador + Miele for the luxury custom-kitchen buyer. SKS fills that gap with a coordinated lineup, wall oven, range, cooktop, refrigerator (including column-style integrated refrigeration competing with Sub-Zero), dishwasher, ventilation, and specialty categories including sous vide oven.</p>
    <p>For LA service, SKS benefits from the LG parent relationship in parts infrastructure, SKS parts share distribution network with the broader LG service chain, which gives SKS strong parts availability relative to other recently-launched luxury brands. Common SKS parts run 2-4 day lead; specialty SKS-specific components 3-7 days. The LG-derived engineering means control platforms, sensor conventions, and service diagnostic patterns follow LG family conventions adapted to SKS's luxury specifications.</p>
  </div></section>

  <section class="section alt"><div class="wrap">
    <h2>SKS wall oven models we service</h2>
    <div class="model-grid">
      <div class="model-card"><h3>SKS 30" single built-in wall oven</h3><p>Luxury-tier single-cavity wall oven. SKS-specific control platform, premium convection, integrated-kitchen aesthetic. Service: bake element, convection fan, control board, sensors, door hardware.</p></div>
      <div class="model-card"><h3>SKS 30" double built-in wall oven</h3><p>Stacked dual-cavity configuration. Upper + lower independent elements + sensors, shared primary control board.</p></div>
      <div class="model-card"><h3>SKS Steam+Convection variants</h3><p>Combi-steam capability with water reservoir + humidity management. LA hard-water service cadence awareness.</p></div>
      <div class="model-card"><h3>Smart-feature integration</h3><p>LG SmartThinQ-compatible Wi-Fi + app control. Firmware + connectivity service layer. Most smart-feature issues resolve without hardware replacement.</p></div>
      <div class="model-card"><h3>Sous vide oven (separate page)</h3><p>Distinct SKS product category with specialized precision-cooking architecture. Covered on dedicated page: <a href="/brands/signature-kitchen-suite-sous-vide-oven-repair/">SKS sous vide oven repair</a>.</p></div>
      <div class="model-card"><h3>Self-clean cycle service</h3><p>Standard pyrolytic self-clean on current SKS wall oven generations. Door-lock motor, thermal sensor, cycle firmware.</p></div>
    </div>
  </div></section>

  <section class="section"><div class="wrap narrow">
    <h2>Common SKS wall oven faults</h2>
    <p><b>Bake element failure</b>, SKS element lasts 8-12 years typical. Replacement $380-$620.</p>
    <p><b>Convection fan motor wear</b>, $420-$680.</p>
    <p><b>Control board lockout</b>, factory reset resolves some; replacement $560-$920 when not.</p>
    <p><b>Smart-feature connectivity issues</b>, usually firmware + network layer. Service $180-$320.</p>
    <p><b>Steam+Convection water reservoir service</b>, $280-$460.</p>
